VCardBuilder gaia::vcard::VCardBuilder::appendNameProperties ( const gaia::base::Array< content::ContentValues > &  contentValuesList)

Appends one line of name informations from the array of ContentValues.

For safety, we'll emit just one value around StructuredName, as external importers may get confused with multiple "N", "FN", etc. properties, though it is valid in vCard spec.

VCardBuilder gaia::vcard::VCardBuilder::appendSipAddresses ( const gaia::base::Array< content::ContentValues > &  contentValuesList)

To append one line of sip address informations from the array of ContentValues.

SIP (Session Initiation Protocol) is first supported in RFC 4770 as part of IMPP support. vCard 2.1 and old vCard 3.0 may not able to parse it, or expect X-SIP instead of "IMPP;sip:...".

We honor RFC 4770 and don't allow vCard 3.0 to emit X-SIP at all.
